================================================================================
MODULE: Buzzer Driver (STM32F1 HAL)
================================================================================

1. FILES
--------
- buzzer.h : Header file containing function prototypes.
- buzzer.c : Implementation of frequency generation and melodies.

2. HARDWARE SETUP
-----------------
- Pin: GPIOA, Pin 5.
- Timer: Requires an initialized TIM_HandleTypeDef (e.g., TIM4).
- Note: The timer must be configured to count in microseconds for the 
  delay_us() function to provide accurate frequencies.

3. FUNCTIONS
------------
- Buzzer_Init: Starts the hardware timer and links the handle.
- Buzzer_Tick: Short 1000Hz chirp (5ms).
- Buzzer_Short: Standard 1000Hz beep (50ms).
- Buzzer_Confirm: Two-tone success melody (1800Hz -> 2200Hz).
- Buzzer_Startup: Three-tone power-on sequence.

4. IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS
-------------------------
The driver uses a blocking "playTone" function that toggles the GPIO pin 
high and low based on the requested frequency. It uses 
__HAL_TIM_GET_COUNTER to create precise microsecond delays.

================================================================================
